HOW TO USE THE SHIPPING ESTIMATOR
I. Find the approximate distance. Use map on other side to
locate shipping and destination points, (or nearest airline
cities to these points). Pull out sliding part of estimator and
use proper scale (depending on direction in which shipment
is being made) to determine approximate airline distance
between airline cities.
2: Find the approximate hours. Directly under each mileage
scale is another scale showing the approximate hours between
airport cities. There are separate seales for Eastbound, West-
bound and North or Southbound shipments. By referring to
the proper scale you can determine the approximate air
time for your shipment.
3. Find the approximate cost. Re-insert the slide and pull it to
set the weight of your shipment in the top window. Read
down to proper distance and you will find the approximate
cost in the window opposite the distance.
